# TypeScript & React

## TypeScript

- Strict types for API request/response shapes; export shared types from `types/index.ts`.
- Interfaces for component props; infer locals where obvious.

## Next.js

- App Router only (not Pages Router).
- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only when needed (state, effects, browser APIs).
- Absolute imports via `@/` path alias.

## Components

- Functional components; one component per file (PascalCase filename).
- Extract reusable logic to hooks; keep components single-purpose.
- Base UI on ShadCN in `components/ui/`; page shells: `PageShell`, `PageLoader`, `ContentCard`.
- Pipeline pages colocate step UI under `app/<step>/`.

## Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities/libs: `camelCase.ts` (e.g. `ollama.ts`, `comfyui.ts`)
- API folders: lowercase with hyphens

## State

- Step data in `sessionStorage` (`lib/pipeline-storage.ts`), not URL query fallbacks for config/description.
- Local UI state with hooks; lift only when necessary.
